    <sharedstimuli>
        <sharedstimulus id="assets/d67a0fbc6332833346765/passage NEW.xml">
            <label key="ceffd00ce96b04a1c590a2b7dbb3fcbc">
                <text>Magnetic Cleaners</text>
            </label>
            <label key="0117aec78d6177811e8fe9a5f0b01a1f">
                <text>Iron filings are small pieces of iron produced by filing or cutting iron.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e8073df0f7fb145a187a3e05d3384776">
                <text>A metalworking factory uses four machines with permanent magnets to collect iron filings that are evenly distributed across the factory floor. The machines roam about the factory floor all day. Two of the four machines are shown below.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="59cfa26c741d65f06e84a3afb4583677">
                <text>magnet</text>
            </label>
            <label key="402154b4e743ac85fc5c2f60e4f249da">
                <text>control and power box</text>
            </label>
            <label key="8d9c307cb7f3c4a32822a51922d1ceaa">
                <text>N</text>
            </label>
            <label key="5dbc98dcc983a70728bd082d1a47546e">
                <text>S</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f16d11db3d019bbbd42dd8b38a76fa43">
                <text>The four machines travel at the same speed and have identical magnets, but they have the following design differences:</text>
            </label>
            <label key="96301de4b02dde60210952b46da649f9">
                <text>differently sized wheels (which affects the height of the magnet above the ground)</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fde95ad8522dd48231f8bdd1f4585614">
                <text>the orientation of the magnet’s north pole (upwards or downwards)</text>
            </label>
            <label key="eea98054464620e0990012a74f6ec157">
                <text>the location of the control box.</text>
            </label>
        </sharedstimulus>
        <sharedstimulus id="assets/83ed01426418d9c036972/passage NEW 9.xml">
            <label key="1d2f76bcffc20eaf4a6fde32a247115a">
                <text>Magnetic Cleaners </text>
            </label>
            <label key="29a0248cdb96ef74d55c040f125ffe07">
                <text>You are responsible for improving the removal of metal filing waste from the floor of a metal working factory. </text>
            </label>
            <label key="fe5f1e3f5edbace32f78f170840f3b77">
                <text>The factory works with several different metals, including iron. Removal of metal waste with the current magnetic cleaners is not effective for all types of metal waste. As a result, the floors must be swept frequently with a brush to collect and remove the other metal waste.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="9db48ee2b9978245610378a5c30c5a4a">
                <text>You want to design a method that will improve the removal of all metal waste.</text>
            </label>
        </sharedstimulus>
    </sharedstimuli>
